PROMPT == ..ATTRIBUTE: Browser Cache
DECLARE
  a CLOB;
  b CLOB;
  c CLOB;
  d CLOB;
  e CLOB;
BEGIN

a := null;
b:=b||'<p><strong>Browser Cache</strong> dictates how the user&#39;s browser will store a rendered APEX Page in the browser&#39;s cache. Normally, browsers save the contents of an application&#39;s pages, however if the cache is disabled, the browser will not save the information and will be forced to reload the information from the server.</p>'||chr(10)||
''||chr(10)||
'<p>From a security standpoint, <strong>Browser Cache</stron';

b:=b||'g> should be <em><strong>disabled</strong></em> so that no sensitive information will not be kept at the browser level. Setting this to &quot;Disabled&quot; will also help prevent subtle back button issues.</p>'||chr(10)||
''||chr(10)||
'<p><strong>NOTE</strong>: When <strong>Browser Cache</strong> is set to &quot;Disabled&quot;, APEX will include the HTTP Header directive <strong><em>cache-control: no-store</em></strong><';

b:=b||'strong><em> </em></strong>indicating the browser should not store page content in either memory or disk. This feature will only work with browsers which support the <em><strong>cache-control</strong></em> directive.</p>'||chr(10)||
'';

c:=c||'<p>To alter the value of <strong>Browser Cache</strong> for a specific page:</p>'||chr(10)||
''||chr(10)||
'<ol>'||chr(10)||
'	<li>Edit the page attributes for the page in question by&nbsp;clicking&nbsp;on it&#39;s name in the&nbsp;<u>Page Rendering</u>&nbsp;tree.</li>'||chr(10)||
'	<li>In the Security region, alter the value for the <strong>Browser Cache</strong> select list.</li>'||chr(10)||
'	<li>Click <strong>Save</strong>.</li>'||chr(10)||
'</ol>'||chr(10)||
''||chr(10)||
'<p>Browser Cache has ';

c:=c||'three possible settings:</p>'||chr(10)||
''||chr(10)||
'<p><strong>- Application Default</strong> - This will take its value from the current application&#39;s Browser Cache attribute.<br />'||chr(10)||
'<strong>- Enabled</strong> - Allows the browser to cache information from the page<br />'||chr(10)||
'<strong>- Disabled</strong> - Prohibits the browser from caching information for the specific page.</p>'||chr(10)||
''||chr(10)||
'<p>The page level <strong>Browser Cache</';

c:=c||'strong> setting, other than Application Default,&nbsp; will override what is defined at the Application level.</p>'||chr(10)||
''||chr(10)||
'<p><strong>NOTE</strong>: When <strong>Browser Cache</strong> is set to &quot;Disabled&quot;, APEX will include the HTTP Header directive <strong><em>cache-control: no-store</em></strong><strong><em> </em></strong>indicating the browser should not store page content in either memory ';

c:=c||'or disk. This feature will only work with browsers which support the <em><strong>cache-control</strong></em> directive.</p>'||chr(10)||
'';

